SIMPLE: snowbird
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snowbird
<hw>Snow"bird</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An arctic finch (<spn>Plectrophenax nivalis</spn> syn.
<spn>Plectrophanes nivalis</spn>) common, in winter, both in
<geog>Europe</geog> and the <country>United States</country>, and often
appearing in large flocks during snowstorms. It is partially white, but
variously marked with chestnut and brown. Called also <altname>snow
bunting</altname>, <altname>snowflake</altname>,
<altname>snowfleck</altname>, and <altname>snowflight</altname>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any finch of the genus <gen>Junco</gen> which appears
in flocks in winter time, especially <spn>Junco hyemalis</spn> in the
Eastern United States; -- called also <altname>blue snowbird</altname>.
See <er>Junco</er>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The fieldfare.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snow-blind</ent>⟦br⟧
